      </table-wrap>
      <p>The number of polymorphisms identified on each chromosome was highly correlated (<italic toggle="yes">r</italic><sup>2</sup> = 0.92) with its physical length. Distribution of polymorphisms showed their slightly higher incidence towards the chromosome ends. This distribution correlates with chromosome coverage by reads (<xref rid="pcbi.1008980.g006" ref-type="fig">Fig 6</xref>), which is related to the fact that GBS targets mostly gene-rich regions, such as chromosome ends, by the use of methylation-sensitive restriction enzymes (e.g. <italic toggle="yes">Ape</italic>KI used in this study).</p>
